{
    "publish_date": "2012-08-03T14:46:29.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT7M13S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "BRADY HARAN: I&#39;m in the middle\nof London on Regent Street--", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "0.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in case you couldn&#39;t tell with\nall those red buses going by.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "2.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We want to talk about something", 
            "dur": "1.02", 
            "start": "5.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a little bit Olympics.", 
            "dur": "0.9", 
            "start": "6.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re going to talk to\nyou about flags.", 
            "dur": "2.14", 
            "start": "6.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s loads of flags up the\nstreet there, but we want to", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "9.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "talk about one in particular.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "11.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s one you don&#39;t often see at\nthe Games, because, well,", 
            "dur": "3.079", 
            "start": "13.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this country&#39;s never actually\nwon a medal.", 
            "dur": "1.886", 
            "start": "16.329"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But their flag?", 
            "dur": "1.335", 
            "start": "18.215"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Very mathematical.", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "19.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: We got chatting\nabout countries and", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "21.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their flags and things.", 
            "dur": "1.45", 
            "start": "23.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I thought, well,\nwhat sort of maths", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "25.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could we do with that?", 
            "dur": "1.05", 
            "start": "27.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we could look at the\nsymmetry of flags and which", 
            "dur": "3.22", 
            "start": "28.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has the most symmetrical flag.", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "31.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then I thought, no.", 
            "dur": "0.84", 
            "start": "33.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I know what the most\nmathematical flag is.", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "34.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this is amazing.", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "37.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So Nepal, I reckon, has the most\nmathematical flag-- the", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "38.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "country of Nepal.", 
            "dur": "1.35", 
            "start": "41.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because the mathematical\nconstruction for the flag is", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "43.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "actually written into\ntheir constitution.", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "46.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ve got it here.", 
            "dur": "1.23", 
            "start": "49.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is Article 5 of the Nepal\nConstitution, where it", 
            "dur": "4.03", 
            "start": "51.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "describes how to construct\nthe nation&#39;s flag.", 
            "dur": "3.64", 
            "start": "55.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Shall I read it to you?", 
            "dur": "1.19", 
            "start": "58.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Schedule 1, relating\nto Article 5.", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "59.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "National flag.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "62.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A, method of making the shape\ninside the border.", 
            "dur": "4.21", 
            "start": "64.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, on the lower portion of a\ncrimson cloth, draw a line AB", 
            "dur": "6.28", 
            "start": "68.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the required length\nfrom left to right.", 
            "dur": "3.03", 
            "start": "74.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two, from A draw a line AC\nperpendicular to AB, making AC", 
            "dur": "6.67", 
            "start": "77.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "equal to AB plus one third AB.", 
            "dur": "3.68", 
            "start": "84.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From AC, mark off D, making a\nline AD equal to line AB.", 
            "dur": "6.98", 
            "start": "88.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Join BD.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "95.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From BD, mark off E, making\nBE equal to AB.", 
            "dur": "5.08", 
            "start": "96.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Four, touching E, draw a line\nFG starting from the point F", 
            "dur": "6.79", 
            "start": "102.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on line AC parallel to AB\nto the right-hand side.", 
            "dur": "5.11", 
            "start": "108.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mark off FG equal to AB.", 
            "dur": "3.8", 
            "start": "113.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Five, join CG.", 
            "dur": "2.59", 
            "start": "117.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I believe it is the only flag\nfor a country, certainly, that", 
            "dur": "5.67", 
            "start": "120.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "isn&#39;t a square or a rectangle.", 
            "dur": "1.61", 
            "start": "126"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It makes it very unusual that\nNepal are bucking the trend.", 
            "dur": "3.97", 
            "start": "127.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;re sticking with it.", 
            "dur": "1.06", 
            "start": "131.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is their flag.", 
            "dur": "0.85", 
            "start": "132.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And they&#39;re sticking with it.", 
            "dur": "1.14", 
            "start": "133.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From AB, mark off AH, making\nAH equal to one", 
            "dur": "5.52", 
            "start": "134.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fourth of line AB.", 
            "dur": "2.23", 
            "start": "140.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And starting from H, draw a line\nHI parallel to line AC,", 
            "dur": "6.23", 
            "start": "142.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touching line CG at point I. If\nit was on cloth, we could", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "148.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "just fold it in half and\nmark it, you see?", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "153.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So maybe I&#39;ll do that\nwith the paper.", 
            "dur": "2.144", 
            "start": "156.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I want to draw half\nthis distance.", 
            "dur": "3.366", 
            "start": "158.264"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Bisect CF at J and draw a line\nJK parallel to AB, touching CG", 
            "dur": "8.35", 
            "start": "161.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at point K. It is not necessary\nto have to measure", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "169.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with your ruler.", 
            "dur": "1.11", 
            "start": "174.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can follow these\ninstructions without any", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "175.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "measuring at all.", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "177.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s telling you to divide\nthings by half and quarters", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "179.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and thirds.", 
            "dur": "1.13", 
            "start": "182.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And using those rules, without\nmeasuring, we should be able", 
            "dur": "4.44", 
            "start": "183.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to do this.", 
            "dur": "0.9", 
            "start": "187.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let L be the point where lines\nJK and HI cut one another.", 
            "dur": "6.11", 
            "start": "188.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nine, join JG.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "194.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "10, let M be the point\nwhere line JG", 
            "dur": "3.93", 
            "start": "197.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and HI cut one another.", 
            "dur": "2.59", 
            "start": "201.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center M and with a\ndistance shortest from M to", 
            "dur": "3.83", 
            "start": "203.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BD, mark off--", 
            "dur": "1.49", 
            "start": "207.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I can&#39;t keep a straight face.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "209.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK.", 
            "dur": "0.74", 
            "start": "210.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center M and with a\ndistance shortest from M to", 
            "dur": "3.64", 
            "start": "211.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BD, mark off N to the lower\nportion of line HI.", 
            "dur": "5.11", 
            "start": "215.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Touching M and starting from O,\na point on AC, draw a line", 
            "dur": "6.39", 
            "start": "220.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from left to right\nparallel to AB.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "226.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center L and radius LN,\ndraw a semicircle on the lower", 
            "dur": "6.26", 
            "start": "229.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "portion and let P and Q be the\npoints where it touches the", 
            "dur": "5.09", 
            "start": "235.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "line OM respectively.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "240.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center M and radius MQ,\ndraw a semicircle on the lower", 
            "dur": "5.32", 
            "start": "243.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "portion touching P and Q. With\ncenter N and radius NM, draw", 
            "dur": "7.25", 
            "start": "249.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an arc touching PNQ at\nR and S. Join RS.", 
            "dur": "7.23", 
            "start": "256.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let T be the point where RS\nand HI cut one another.", 
            "dur": "5.18", 
            "start": "263.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "16, with center T and radius TS,\ndraw a semicircle on the", 
            "dur": "7.41", 
            "start": "268.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "upper portion of PNQ, touching\nit at two points.", 
            "dur": "4.74", 
            "start": "276.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is what mathematics was\nlike in ancient times.", 
            "dur": "5.11", 
            "start": "281.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is what it was like\nto the Greeks.", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "286.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All Greek mathematics\nwas like this and", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "287.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "written down like this.", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "290.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center T and radius TM,\ndraw an arc on the upper", 
            "dur": "4.99", 
            "start": "291.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "portion of PNQ, touching\nat two points.", 
            "dur": "3.901", 
            "start": "296.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eight equal and similar\ntriangles of the moon are to", 
            "dur": "3.565", 
            "start": "300.451"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be made in the space lying\ninside the semicircle of", 
            "dur": "4.034", 
            "start": "304.016"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "number 16 and outside the arc of\nnumber 17 of this schedule.", 
            "dur": "6.48", 
            "start": "308.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I made that bit up.", 
            "dur": "0.92", 
            "start": "314.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(WHISPERING) I cheated\nthere a little bit.", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "315.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just a little bit.", 
            "dur": "0.99", 
            "start": "317.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "C, method of making the sun.", 
            "dur": "2.84", 
            "start": "318.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Bisect line AF at U and draw a\nline UV parallel to line AB,", 
            "dur": "6.37", 
            "start": "321.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touching line BE at V.\nI&#39;ve gone blind.", 
            "dur": "3.732", 
            "start": "327.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh, it&#39;s all swimming now.", 
            "dur": "2.908", 
            "start": "331.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK.", 
            "dur": "0.53", 
            "start": "334.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center W, the point where\nHI and UV cut one another, and", 
            "dur": "4.88", 
            "start": "334.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "radius MN draw a circle.", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "339.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Got to W. There isn&#39;t\nany X and Z, so yes,", 
            "dur": "3.89", 
            "start": "342.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re nearly there.", 
            "dur": "1.06", 
            "start": "345.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It took that many\nletters, though.", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "347.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It took nearly the\nwhole alphabet.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "348.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just be glad there\naren&#39;t 27 steps.", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "351.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What we would have done then.", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "353.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With center W and radius\nLN, draw a circle.", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "354.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "12 equal and similar triangles\nof the sun are to be made in", 
            "dur": "4.72", 
            "start": "359.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the space enclosed by the\ncircles of number 20 and of", 
            "dur": "4.27", 
            "start": "363.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "number 21 and with the two\napexes of two triangles", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "368.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "touching line HI.", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "372.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "D, method of making\nthe border.", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "374.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The width of the border will be\nequal to the width of TN.", 
            "dur": "4.14", 
            "start": "376.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This will be of deep blue color\nand will be provided on", 
            "dur": "4.05", 
            "start": "380.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all sides of the flag.", 
            "dur": "1.79", 
            "start": "384.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "However, on the five angles of\nthe flag, the external angles", 
            "dur": "4.33", 
            "start": "386.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "will be equal to the\ninternal angles.", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "391.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Explanation--", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "393.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the lines HI, RS, FE, ED, JG,\nOQ, JK, UV are imaginary.", 
            "dur": "6.3", 
            "start": "395.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Similarly, the external and\ninternal circles of the sun", 
            "dur": "3.61", 
            "start": "401.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the other arcs, except\nthe crescent", 
            "dur": "2.48", 
            "start": "405.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "moon, are also imaginary.", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "407.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These are not shown\non the flag.", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "410.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s as easy as it sounds.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "412.72"
        }
    ], 
